@zmi1 your problem is another thing... 
it's that there is no pg_hba.conf entry for host "2001:our:ipv6:addr", user "testuser", database "postgres"...

you can either specify this in the pg_hba or give to oc an existing db (that may give you problems too ... the fix is waiting review here #867

@emerzh yes i know, but that's no bug, it's a feature: we are an isp, so we implement solutions for many customers. and i can't give rights for "testuser" to "postgres", no chance for that. no package should ever need to have this, see typo3, joomla, wordpress etc., none of them need "postgres" access.

your process should be changed: you can try to set the rights, but if there's no right to "postgres", just ignore it, you can warn the user if you like - but don't stop here. we've already setup "testuser" to have full rights on the "owncloud" database, that must be enough.

it was you who wrote pull request #697, i thought that this would be the solution already. so it seems there should be another fix.
